-- U.K.’s Carmichael Says Independent Scotland Could Lose the Pound
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g
-- 2013-11-24T09:47:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-24/u-k-s-carmichael-says-independent-scotland-could-lose-the-pound.html
Scotland could lose the right to use the pound if voters choose independence from the rest of the U.K., said Alistair Carmichael, the U.K. Secretary of State for Scotland.  “Currency union would not work,” Carmichael said on BBC Television’s “Andrew Marr Show” today.  To contact the reporter on this story: Simon Kennedy in London at  skennedy4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Mike Harrison at  mharrison5@bloomberg.net  